From 90fb376415fdd9c3ee500bdf2a175c2bda6b3309 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Manish Dharanenthiran <mdharane@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 11 Aug 2025 17:25:31 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:PROTOCOL:hostapd: Update re-assoc mechanism frequency
 list

In split-phy case, in-order to identify whether the corressponding AP
has split-phy enabled, frequency list from wiphy info will be used.
For 5 GHz high band, start frequency was checked between 5490 and 5895.
With the latest upgrade, the start frequency was updated from 5490 to
5895. Because of this update, conditional logic is failing to enable
split-phy even if the AP is powered up in split-phy radio.

Fix this by updating the frequency logic to include both start and end
frequencies instead of checking the in-between range.

Signed-off-by: Manish Dharanenthiran <mdharane@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 wpa_supplicant/events.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/wpa_supplicant/events.c b/wpa_supplicant/events.c
index 7105840..95b4cb2 100644
--- a/wpa_supplicant/events.c
+++ b/wpa_supplicant/events.c
@@ -4282,10 +4282,10 @@ static bool is_all_links_associated(struct wpa_supplicant *wpa_s)
 	for (i = 0; i < wpa_s->num_multi_hws; i++) {
 		struct hostapd_multi_hw_info *hw_info = &wpa_s->multi_hw_info[i];
 
-		if(hw_info->start_freq > 5925 && hw_info->end_freq < 6425)
+		if(hw_info->start_freq >= 5925 && hw_info->end_freq <= 6425)
 			is_split_phy_6ghz = true;
 
-		if (hw_info->start_freq > 5490 && hw_info->end_freq < 5895)
+		if (hw_info->start_freq >= 5490 && hw_info->end_freq <= 5895)
 			is_split_phy_5ghz = true;
 	}
 	i = 0;
-- 
2.34.1

